From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Keyur Maru <kd2maru@gmail.com>
Date: Fri, 10 Jul 2026 19:12:09 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] SystemUI: toggle the torch for single-strength flashlights

On devices whose flash reports a single strength level (Binary state) - e.g.
sdm632 / Moto G7 Play - the flashlight QS tile only supports CLICK and shows no
strength slider, so a plain click was a no-op. Toggle the torch directly for the
Binary case.

Change-Id: I65307410846c16c88ee137348048de145eb94985
---
 .../FlashlightTileUserActionInteractor.kt     | 21 ++++++++++++-------
 1 file changed, 13 insertions(+), 8 deletions(-)

diff --git a/packages/SystemUI/src/com/android/systemui/qs/tiles/impl/flashlight/domain/interactor/FlashlightTileUserActionInteractor.kt b/packages/SystemUI/src/com/android/systemui/qs/tiles/impl/flashlight/domain/interactor/FlashlightTileUserActionInteractor.kt
index 9ad7bc01bdbb..140d4b776578 100644
--- a/packages/SystemUI/src/com/android/systemui/qs/tiles/impl/flashlight/domain/interactor/FlashlightTileUserActionInteractor.kt
+++ b/packages/SystemUI/src/com/android/systemui/qs/tiles/impl/flashlight/domain/interactor/FlashlightTileUserActionInteractor.kt
@@ -44,14 +44,19 @@ constructor(
             when (action) {
                 is QSTileUserAction.Click -> {
                     if (FlashlightStrength.isEnabled) {
-                        if (
-                            !ActivityManager.isUserAMonkey() &&
-                                input.data is FlashlightModel.Available.Level
-                        ) {
-                            // Note: no Click response for Binary state. See ToggleClick.
-                            flashlightInteractor.get().setEnabled(true)
-                            // the ui code runs on the main thread
-                            flashlightDialogDelegate.get().showDialog(input.action.expandable)
+                        if (!ActivityManager.isUserAMonkey()) {
+                            if (input.data is FlashlightModel.Available.Level) {
+                                flashlightInteractor.get().setEnabled(true)
+                                // the ui code runs on the main thread
+                                flashlightDialogDelegate.get().showDialog(input.action.expandable)
+                            } else if (input.data is FlashlightModel.Available.Binary) {
+                                // Binary flashes have no adjustable strength and therefore no
+                                // slider dialog, and the tile only supports CLICK (not
+                                // TOGGLE_CLICK), so a plain click must toggle the torch here.
+                                // Without this branch the tile is a no-op on devices whose flash
+                                // reports a single strength level (e.g. sdm632 / Moto G7 Play).
+                                flashlightInteractor.get().setEnabled(!input.data.enabled)
+                            }
                         }
                     } else { // preserve old behavior at the cost of some redundancy
                         if (
